description.narrative:
Support to the local population affected by the pipeline Niger-Benin installation
This project aims to support the local populations affected by the crossing of the pipeline Niger-Benin over a distance of 150km. the project proposes to map the impacts associated with the installation of the pipeline through informing and raising awareness among neighboring populations in order to help them better understand these impacts and the behavior to be observed. It will be executed for 6 months as a pilot.
In addition, beyond information and awareness-raising, vigilance and monitoring committees composed mainly of young people and women will be set up in the communities and a joint synergy by all affected communities will be created through the implementation
- This pilot project will concern a limited number of local authorities affected by the Niger-Benin pipeline. For Zinder region,  Tesker is affected by the pipeline for about  212 km;
- As of Tahoua , the municipality of Allela is crossed by the pipelinefor 51 km;
- The region of Maradi, Ourafane, is also affected  by the pipeline for 60 km;
- Lastly, Dan Kassari  in Dosso region is also crossed by the pipeline for 59 km.
The choice of municipalities was made on the basis of the longest crossing areain each region.
